## Solution 1: Fix Detection Logic for New Metadata Format

Update `looksLikeDevlogIssue()` to detect our new base64 metadata format:

```typescript
private looksLikeDevlogIssue(issue: GitHubIssue): boolean {
  // Check for devlog labels
  const hasDevlogLabels = issue.labels.some((label: any) =>
    label.name.startsWith(this.config.labelsPrefix)
  );

  // Check for new metadata format
  const hasDevlogMetadata = issue.body?.includes('<!-- DEVLOG_METADATA:') ?? false;

  // Legacy patterns (for backward compatibility)
  const hasLegacyStructure = 
    issue.body?.includes('## Business Context') ||
    issue.body?.includes('## Technical Context') ||
    issue.body?.includes('<!-- DEVLOG_HTML_FORMAT_V1 -->');

  return hasDevlogLabels || hasDevlogMetadata || hasLegacyStructure;
}
```

## Solution 2: Improve Search Query Robustness

Make search more flexible by:
- Using broader label patterns
- Adding OR conditions for multiple identification methods
- Graceful degradation when labels are missing

## Solution 3: Hybrid Approach

1. **Try metadata-based detection first** (fastest)
2. **Fall back to label-based search** if needed
3. **Final fallback to full list + filtering** only as last resort

## Solution 4: Add Devlog Marker Label

Automatically add a simple marker label (e.g., `devlog`) to all devlog issues for reliable identification.
